a state superior court judge last week suspended actions on civil lawsuits stemming from the january 2000 dormitory fire at seton hall university until a grand jury has completed its investigation of the fire suits have been filed by the families of the 3 freshmen who were killed and by 5 of the 58 others injured in the blaze at the south orange campus the grand jury empaneled in october 2001 will decide if homicide and arson charges should be filed and if seton hall 's lack of security and numerous fire code violations played a role in the fire the panel is expected to meet through september john holl

